{{refimprove|date=March 2024}} The '''Matsumae Domain''' (松前藩), a prominent domain during the [[Edo period]], was situated in Matsumae, [[Matsumae Island]] (Ishijima), which is currently known as Matsumae Town, [[Matsumae District, Hokkaido|Matsumae District]], Hokkaido, via [[Tsugaru District, Mutsu|Tsugaru District]], [[Oshima Province]]. The clan's leader, also known as the lord of the domain, constructed [[Matsumae Castle|Matsumae]] Fukuyama Castle in the same location and henceforth, the clan came to be referred to as the Fukuyama clan. In 1868, the castle was relocated to Tatejo in Assabu-cho, Hiyama-gun, within the territory, and was known as Tatehan during the [[Meiji era|Meiji period]]. Initially, the Matsumae clan's jurisdiction was limited to the Wajin territory on the [[Oshima Peninsula]] in southwest Hokkaido. However, they gradually expanded their control over the Ezo region, which is now part of Hokkaido, and transformed it into their domain. The clan's economic foundation relied on their exclusive trade with the [[Ainu people]] of Ezo, which set them apart from the agricultural-based governance principles of the [[Tokugawa shogunate|Shogunate]] system. Towards the end of the [[Edo period]], the shogunate often assumed control over Ezo.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Howell |first=David L. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3bjADwAAQBAJ&dq=Matsumae+Domain&pg=PA33 |title=Capitalism From Within: Economy, Society, and the State in a Japanese Fishery |date=2018-05-04 |publisher=Univ of California Press |isbn=978-0-520-30158-0 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Siddle |first=Richard M. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=W5DKfJsPv2sC&dq=Matsumae+Domain&pg=PT47 |title=Race, Resistance and the Ainu of Japan |date=2012-06-14 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-134-82680-3 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Bailey |first=Scott C. M. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9VzbEAAAQBAJ&dq=Matsumae+Domain&pg=PT92 |title=Russia and Japan in the Sea of Okhotsk: A Global History of Maritime Travel and Cultural Encounters, 1600-1900 |date=2023-12-01 |publisher=Taylor & Francis |isbn=978-1-003-81876-2 |language=en}}</ref> {{short description|Japanese feudal domain located in Hokkaidō Province}} {{Infobox former subdivision |_noautocat = |native_name = 松前藩 |conventional_long_name = Matsumae Domain |common_name = Matsumae Domain |subdivision = [[Han system|Han]] |nation = |status_text = [[Han system|Domain]] of Japan |government_type = Daimyō <!-- General information --> |capital = [[Matsumae Castle]] |coordinates = |political_subdiv = <!-- Accepts wikilinks --> |today = [[Aomori Prefecture]] <!-- Rise and fall, events, years and dates --> <!-- Only fill in the start/end event entry if a specific article exists. Don't just say "abolition" or "declaration". --> |year_start = 1590 |year_end = 1871 |event_start = |date_start = |event_end = <!-- Default: "Disestablished" --> |date_end = <!-- Optional: Date of disestablishment --> |event1 = |date_event1 = |event2 = |date_event2 = |event3 = |date_event3 = |event4 = |date_event4 = |event5 = |date_event5 = |life_span = |era = Edo period |event_pre = <!-- Optional: A crucial event that took place before before "event_start" --> |date_pre = |event_post = <!-- Optional: A crucial event that took place before after "event_end" --> |date_post = <!-- Images --> |image_flag = <!-- Default: Flag of {{{common_name}}}.svg --> |image_border = <!-- Default: "border"; for non-rectangular flag, type "no" --> |flag_type = <!-- Displayed text for link under flag. Default "Flag" --> |flag = <!-- Link target under flag image. Default: Flag of {{{common_name}}} --> |image_coat = File:Maru ni Takedabishi (No background and Black color drawing).svg |symbol_type = ''[[Mon (emblem)|Mon]]'' of the [[Matsumae clan]] |symbol = <!-- Link target under symbol image. Default: Coat of arms of {{{common_name}}} --> |image_map = MatsumaeJo.jpg |image_map_caption = Restored castle tower of Matsumae Castle <!-- 